column14:
The principal clients of the project are businesses the great majority of which are digitally competent and prefer digital communications and delivery of council services.  It is anticipated that business groups will have no difficulty in accessibility to a digital solution for their needs.

The Council is on a journey to achieve a digital shift in the provision of all of its services and provides a comprehensive we-page to enable all segments of the community to make contact and access.  Whilst the Council has simplified the digital journey to services and enabled the widest possible access, there is a recognition that not all, particularly elderly and vulnerable individuals of not use digital media to address their needs.  The council has policies to ensure inclusion for all groups within the Redbridge community, whatever their needs may be.  Alternatives to digital first are ultimately available although the emphasis for digital access remains and is an aim for all services

&nbsp;

column13:
&nbsp;
<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;line-height: normal"><span lang="EN"><span style="font-family: Arial;font-size: medium">User research to gain insight into users experiences and issues will be shared on the user research library.</span></span></p>
